Quarry Creek\n*Quarryville Creek\n*Stenkil\n\n==Course==\nStoney Creek rises on the [[Perkins Run (Delaware River tributary)|Perkins Run]] divide Westwood, Delaware in [[New Castle County, Delaware]].  Stoney Creek then flows southeast to meet the Delaware River at [[Bellevue, Delaware]].<ref name=\"SCTopozone\"/>\n\n==Watershed==\nStoney Creek drains {{convert|2.36|sqmi}} of area, receives about 46.8 in/year of precipitation, has a [[topographic wetness index]] of 475.50 and is about 17.6% forested.<ref name=\"watershed\"/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of rivers of Delaware]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}{{Delaware}}\n\n[[Category:Rivers of Delaware]]\n\n\n{{Delaware-river-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox river\n| name               = Stoney Creek\n| name_native        = \n| name_native_lang   = \n| name_other         = Tributary to Delaware River\n| name_etymology     = \n| nickname\n\n| image              = [[File:Eagle Falls.jpg|thumb|Lenape Falls - Waterfall in Northern Delaware along Stony Creek]]\n| image_size         = \n| image_caption      = \n| image_alt          =\n<!---------------------- MAPS --> \n| map                = \n| map_size           = 180\n| map_caption        = Mouth of Stoney Creek\n| map_alt            = Map of Stoney Creek mouth\n| pushpin_map        = Delaware#USA\n| pushpin_map_size   = 180\n| pushpin_map_caption= \n| pushpin_map_alt    = Location of Stoney Creek mouth\n<!---------------------- LOCATION -->\n| subdivision_type1  = Country\n| subdivision_name1  = United States\n| subdivision_type2  = State\n| subdivision_name2  = Delaware\n| subdivision_type3  = County\n| subdivision_name3  = New Castle\n| subdivision_type4  = \n| subdivision_name4  = \n| subdivision_type5  = \n| subdivision_name5  = \n<!---------------------- PHYSICAL CHARACTERISTICS -->\n| length             = {{convert|3.2|mi|km|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"geoviewer\">{{cite web |title=ArcGIS Web Application |url=https://epa.maps.arcgis.com/apps/webappviewer/index.html?id=a